HEADWORD: Airer
<hw>Air"er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
exposes to the air.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A frame on which clothes are aired or
dried.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>airfield</ent>⟦br⟧
